# Reflection

## What I Learned

High-quality code is not defined solely by correct output. Readability, naming, documentation, and maintainability significantly influence how easily other developers can understand and extend the implementation.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

In a production environment, I would recommend adopting a style guide such as PEP 8, adding automated linting and formatting tools, writing unit tests, and including comprehensive documentation to improve long-term maintainability.

